Terrell executor of Holt v. Atkinson’s executor. In debt on a bill of exchange profert is not necessary. This was an appeal from a judgment of the District Court of Williamsburg, rendered in favor of the appellee, on a bill of exchange. Plea, nil debet. The only question was, whether profert of a bill of exchange in an action of debt is necessary? In this case it was not made. Wickham, for the appellee,

Contended, that it was not necessary, but that if it were, the Statute of Jeofails cured it after verdict

The Court affirmed the judgment.
